cure individual & group file storage may be used to store restricted data as defined by the stanford university information security office support for assistance please submit a helpsu request rates the disk based replication service is available by subscription and is charged monthly to your department's it services bill the cost is based on the amount of file storage required to store the backups see the computing services rates page for more information getting started if you wish to subscribe to the disk based replication service please submit a helpsu request once you have agreed on the replication setup with the storage group place an order via orderit for individual & group file storage or secure individual & group file storage disk space and to cancel any legacy bars services last modified wed 6 jul 2011 at 16 16 pages about this service overview backups for personal purchase desktop backups for departments & workgroups desktop disk based replication backup details backup and recovery service servers bars service details using tsm to restore a file or perform a manual backup data privacy and hipaa compliance software and information for bars administrators anatomy of a tsm scheduler log bars administrators frequently asked questions network throughput by building backup solutions summary chart actions orderit find answers submit a helpsu request stanford answers related pages backup and recovery service servers backups for departments & workgroups desktop backups for personal purchase desktop storage footer links stanford university helpsu user login stanford university terms of use copyright complaints
